alert.note: Alert for Carver; Dakota; Hennepin; Scott (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued May 23 at 10:41AM CDT until May 27 at 4:00PM CDT by NWS Minneapolis
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Minnesota... Minnesota River at Savage affecting Scott, Dakota, Carver and Hennepin Counties. Minnesota River near Jordan affecting Scott, Carver and Sibley Counties. .Rivers have crested and will continue to fall this week. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL SATURDAY AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Minnesota River at Savage. * WHEN...Until Saturday afternoon. * IMPACTS...At 705.0 feet, Flood waters begin to impact the park road at Fort Snelling State Park. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1000 AM CDT Tuesday, the stage was 706.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The river is continuing to fall. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage Friday evening and continue falling to 699.1 feet Tuesday morning. - Flood stage is 702.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 706.1 feet on 05/17/1993. &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
